Date: 5/11/26
Title: BalanceKing Application spec

Description of the problem:
  BalanceKing wants to add tooltips to their plots to make it easier for clients
  to understand. I will create a hardcoded example showing that I understand the
  libraries and how to add tooltips.

Description of files:
  demo.py:
    The main file whose code is shown on the Streamlit webpage. It uses real 
    numbers to show the Plotly library possibilities.

  libTest.py:
    Learning to use the Plotly library on some basic data. 
  polarChartDirections.py:
    Using an example from the internet

Sources used:
  https://plotly.com/python/polar-chart/#webgl-polar-chart
  https://rotorlab.tamu.edu/me459/Rotor%20Balancing/2016%20TPS%20Tut%20ROTOR%20BALANCING%20Pavelek.pdf
  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hn_ORuvQlrE
  https://plotly.com/python/plotly-express/